    },
    {
      "id": "9b0ecef2_b7c72a65",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/charts/so-catalog-db-adapter/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 21,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "AAF cadi core jar allows to generate a keyfile, create a digest of the password using the keyfile. We pass this digest along with keyfile to AAF and AAF, I believe, compares the digest to validate the password. I think AAF java library will also allow us to decrypt using the digest & keyfile. I have not tried it.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4277,
        "name": "Ramesh Parthasarathy",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.parthasarathy@att.com",
        "username": "parthasram"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-04 18:11:01.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0432b6e0_5bb5e07f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3e35e029_05a8e29f",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/charts/so-catalog-db-adapter/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 21,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "where is your keyfile?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-04 18:14:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9b0ecef2_b7c72a65",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d7f2fcf0_a314db17",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/charts/so-catalog-db-adapter/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 21,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "keyfile part of the client certs & is already included in the SO image(s). Here is the link to it https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=so.git;a=commit;h=837beb73d7aa6e8f7e4e932ac71e59663b868992\nunder packages/docker/src/main/docker/docker-files/certs/org.onap.so.keyfile\nI want you to know there are pros and cons in including these files in SO vs OOM repositories. We chose to go with having them in SO images. Hope this helps.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4277,
        "name": "Ramesh Parthasarathy",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.parthasarathy@att.com",
        "username": "parthasram"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-04 18:28:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3e35e029_05a8e29f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "daa4b0c2_979b307d",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/charts/so-catalog-db-adapter/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 21,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "This means that your keyfile is effectively hardcoded in the image which is a very bad practice.\n\nPlease take into account that those images are publically available which means that the whole key encryption is insecure as you are leaking a secret key.\n\nNot to mention that you should use automated aaf certificate generation (see aaf-hello) to avoid storing certificate in any form",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-04 18:31:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d7f2fcf0_a314db17",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "48e68c64_8ed5dd29",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/so/charts/so-catalog-db-adapter/resources/config/overrides/override.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 21,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "I think you are mistaken here. There are client certs and they can become part of the image.\nThe one you seem to refer to is AAF htts certs which will be generated with init container and will become part of OOM repository. I did not want to club AAF (authentication & authorization) with SSL into a single gerrit request. This pull is specifically related to authentication & authorization only. SSL will be dealt after approval of this. Hope this helps.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4277,
        "name": "Ramesh Parthasarathy",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.parthasarathy@att.com",
        "username": "parthasram"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-04 18:40:52.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "daa4b0c2_979b307d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
